description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in Public Health and making a difference to children, young people and their families?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the answer is &#39;yes&#39; then the 0-19 Healthy Child Team are looking to recruit an enthusiastic Admin Assistant to be based at Northallerton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a varied job supporting the Health Visiting &amp; School Nursing teams and Child Health Information Service across North Yorkshire in the delivery of public health interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a team player with effective administration and communication skills to work with staff and service users in order to help in the delivery of an excellent service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At HDFT our values of being respectful, passionate and responsible are at the heart of our practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Please be aware we are advertising for two positions - 1 x 37.5 hours per week, 1 x 30 hours per week, please identify which position you are interested in in your application form**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information please contact Sheila Jenkinson on 07387 527454 or at sheilajenkinson@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**This job advert will close as soon as a sufficient amount of applications have been received. Please apply for this job as soon as you can, if you are interested.**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
